%N A398081 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (zeta(3) - H(k,3)) * H(2*k)/(2*k+1), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,3) = A007408(k)/A007409(k) is the k-th harmonic number of order 3.
%H A398081 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.41, p. 438, eq. (4.136), section 5.41, p. 465, section 6.41, pp. 695-698.
